Police busted three burglars on Saturday caught stealing a
car on Moi Avenue in Mombasa CBD. Police named three suspects as Teresia Wambui,
Daniel Kariuki and Lass Wanjiru who were arrested and taken to Central Police
Station. The three were cornered after they rammed into a
tuk tuk that was driving into other side of the road while escaping with a
stolen car of model Fielder KCH 354E white in color. Also see: Cop arrested over links to carjacking, robberies Members of the public called the police who
arrived at the scene after the accident raised suspicions when the occupants
tried to escape. “We suspect these three persons have been robbing
our people of their hard earned sweet. We are warning that anyone coming to
this town with an aim of committing a crime that their days are numbered,”
Mombasa police commander Johnstone Ipara said while addressing journalists at
Central Police Station where three were paraded. Ipara said they will be paraded at the police
station for the whole weekend for identification Will be paraded for
identification until Monday when they will be presented in court. He said they will be charged with robbery with
violence, causing an accident, failing to stop after causing an accident,
driving on the wrong side of the vehicle. “There is somebody here in town hosting thieves
and we believe that is a cartel. We are looking for those cartels working with
outsiders to cause havoc,” Ipara added. On April this year, police arrested a gang of
four attempting to steal a car in Makadara grounds at Mombasa CBD. Click here for the latest political news